I posted a story about how I'd lost my job, almost lost my home, and that depression was taking over...

...but through many sleepless nights (and tubs of ice cream) I built my writing career to a point where it could actually pay my bills.

Knowing what it's like to be broke as hell, I shared my story to the Imgur community, and gave away a Kindle version of Arena Mode for free.

THEN....SHIT EXPLODED.

Arena Mode became a trilogy, then it was optioned for a streaming series, and NOW I have a sexy new cover, and Heavy Metal Magazine is re-releasing the novel in bookstores worldwide.

Being able to afford fancy luxuries like food and heat are nice, don't get me wrong. But above all else, I made lifelong friends. 

I received so much support from Imgurians that it still makes me tear up to think about it (support I was NOT getting from my family back in 2015)

I can't thank you enough, because I would NOT BE HERE if it wasn't for you.

Love and hugs from Canada xox 
- Blake

--

MOST VIRAL EDIT:

Hail Satan!

Kidding.

At the risk of sounding like an Oscar acceptance speech, THANK YOU again. Love you guys.

If you want to know more about Arena Mode: 
http://www.arenamode.com/

And YES, there will be a shout-out to Imgur when the streaming series drops. That's my only special request for the credits. ;)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/44Ci1Gc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BlakeNorthcott]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Day 279: of cheeseburgers I want inside of me</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/HZM4kiT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DiTmUFR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Andouille Burger

